From fc07c6ce2fca1cde2a8c0a8236a5404c4f914dd4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Felipe Vasconcelos <Felipe.Vasconcelos@windriver.com>
Date: Fri, 8 May 2026 15:36:07 -0300
Subject: [PATCH] Add OAuth2 Proxy headers middleware

Keystone federation expects OIDC claims as WSGI environment
variables (HTTP_OIDC_ISS, HTTP_OIDC_EMAIL, REMOTE_USER) because
it was designed for Apache mod_auth_openidc. OAuth2-Proxy forwards
claims as HTTP headers instead. This middleware bridges the gap by
decoding the JWT access token and mapping claims to the expected
environment variables.

JWT signature verification is intentionally skipped - the trust
boundary is OAuth2-Proxy, which already validated the token.

Signed-off-by: Felipe Vasconcelos <Felipe.Vasconcelos@windriver.com>
---
 keystone/middleware/__init__.py               |   0
 keystone/middleware/oauth2_proxy_headers.py   |  96 ++++++++++++
 keystone/server/flask/application.py          |   4 +
 .../tests/unit/test_oauth2_proxy_headers.py   | 139 ++++++++++++++++++
 4 files changed, 239 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 keystone/middleware/__init__.py
 create mode 100644 keystone/middleware/oauth2_proxy_headers.py
 create mode 100644 keystone/tests/unit/test_oauth2_proxy_headers.py

